# Frontend Patterns

## Component Patterns

### Functional Components with Arrow Functions
All components use arrow function syntax with explicit typing:

```typescript
interface MyComponentProps {
  readonly title: string;
  readonly onClick?: () => void;
}

export const MyComponent = ({ title, onClick }: MyComponentProps) => {
  return <div onClick={onClick}>{title}</div>;
};
```

### Props Interface Naming
- Props interfaces are named `{ComponentName}Props`
- Use `readonly` modifier for all props
- Optional props use `?` suffix

### Component File Structure
```
ComponentName/
├── ComponentName.tsx      # Main component
├── SubComponent.tsx       # Related sub-components
├── index.ts               # Public exports
├── useComponentHook.ts    # Component-specific hooks
└── __tests__/
    └── ComponentName.test.tsx
```

## Hook Patterns

### Custom Hooks
- Prefix with `use`
- Return object for multiple values
- Use `useCallback` for functions passed to children
- Use `useMemo` for expensive computations

```typescript
export const useMyHook = () => {
  const [state, setState] = useState(initialValue);

  const handler = useCallback(() => {
    // logic
  }, [dependencies]);

  return { state, handler };
};
```

### Context Hooks
Pattern for context with hooks:

```typescript
// MyContext.tsx
const MyContext = createContext<MyContextType | null>(null);

export const MyProvider = ({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) => {
  // state and logic
  return <MyContext.Provider value={value}>{children}</MyContext.Provider>;
};

// useMyContext.ts
export const useMyContext = () => {
  const context = useContext(MyContext);
  if (!context) {
    throw new Error('useMyContext must be used within MyProvider');
  }
  return context;
};
```

## State Management Patterns

### Redux Toolkit Slices
```typescript
interface MyState {
  items: Item[];
  loading: boolean;
  error: string | null;
}

const initialState: MyState = {
  items: [],
  loading: false,
  error: null,
};

const mySlice = createSlice({
  name: 'mySlice',
  initialState,
  reducers: {
    setItems: (state, action: PayloadAction<Item[]>) => {
      state.items = action.payload;
    },
  },
  extraReducers: (builder) => {
    builder
      .addCase(fetchItems.pending, (state) => {
        state.loading = true;
      })
      .addCase(fetchItems.fulfilled, (state, action) => {
        state.loading = false;
        state.items = action.payload;
      });
  },
});
```

### Async Thunks
```typescript
export const fetchItems = createAsyncThunk(
  'mySlice/fetchItems',
  async (params: FetchParams) => {
    const response = await apiClient.get('/items', { params });
    return response.data;
  }
);
```

## API Patterns

### API Client Functions
```typescript
export const getItems = async (params?: GetItemsParams): Promise<Item[]> => {
  const response = await apiClient.get('/items', { params });
  return response.data;
};

export const createItem = async (data: CreateItemData): Promise<Item> => {
  const response = await apiClient.post('/items', data);
  return response.data;
};
```

## Testing Patterns

### Component Tests
```typescript
describe('MyComponent', () => {
  it('renders correctly', () => {
    render(<MyComponent title="Test" />);
    expect(screen.getByText('Test')).toBeInTheDocument();
  });

  it('calls onClick handler', () => {
    const onClick = vi.fn();
    render(<MyComponent title="Test" onClick={onClick} />);
    fireEvent.click(screen.getByText('Test'));
    expect(onClick).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
  });
});
```

### Hook Tests
```typescript
describe('useMyHook', () => {
  it('returns initial state', () => {
    const { result } = renderHook(() => useMyHook());
    expect(result.current.state).toBe(initialValue);
  });
});
```

## Styling Patterns

### Tailwind CSS
- Use utility classes directly in JSX
- Use template literals for conditional classes
- Extract common patterns to components

```typescript
const Button = ({ variant, children }: ButtonProps) => {
  const baseClasses = 'px-4 py-2 rounded font-medium';
  const variantClasses = variant === 'primary' 
    ? 'bg-blue-500 text-white' 
    : 'bg-gray-200 text-gray-800';

  return (
    <button className={`${baseClasses} ${variantClasses}`}>
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};
```

## Import Patterns

### Absolute Imports
Use path aliases defined in tsconfig:
```typescript
import { MyComponent } from '@/components/MyComponent';
import { useAuth } from '@/hooks/useAuth';
import { User } from '@/types';
```

### Barrel Exports
Use index.ts for public API:
```typescript
// components/index.ts
export { Button } from './Button';
export { Input } from './Input';
```
